`find_substitue` just tries to find the package with the most matching dependencies. If there are multiple such packages, it picks the last one it saw (meaning the last one alphabetically basically).

It should be using the SAT solver, and at the very least, it should try to return the newest version substitute. This is blocked on https://github.com/conda/conda/issues/454. 

